    <text>
        <body>
            <p>51 <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">BURGENLAND</placeName>
                <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">JEWS</term> MARRONED ON BREAKWATER IN <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">DANUBE</placeName>: 35 REPATRIATED AND ARRESTED BY NAZI. 15 STILL HIDING IN
                WOOD ON FRONTIER.</p>

            <p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <date when="1938-04-20">Apr. 20th</date>. (<orgName
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005433">Jewish Telegraphic agency</orgName>).</p>

            <p>Fifty-one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> from <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName> were rescued on Sunday night from a breakwater in the
                    <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">Danube</placeName> after the inhabitants of the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> town of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Theben</placeName> had been attracted by their cries of distress. The breakwater
                was about 100 meters from the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> side of the
                river. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> frontier guards brought the marooned
                    <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Theben</placeName>.</p>

            <p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, who are from the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName> frontier towns of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName> and <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3059704/jarovce.html">Kroatisch-Jarendorf</placeName>, declared that they had been arrested by
                    <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">Nazi stormtroopers</orgName> who had confiscated their <term
                    type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887">property</term>, put them in a motor-boat and left
                them marooned on the breakwater.</p>

            <p>Among the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> was the 82-year-old <term
                    type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735">Rabbi</term> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_armin">Perls</persName>,
                    <note>im Originaltext fälschlich: <persName>Parls</persName></note> his <term type="subject"
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292">sick</term>
                <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292">wife</term>, and many <term
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and small <term
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>.</p>

            <p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Theben</placeName> innkeeper <persName ref="#ehri_bf_sieber"
                    >Sieber</persName> took pity on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
                and put them up at his inn. They were later fetched by <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html"
                    >Czecho-Slovak</placeName>
                <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119">police</term> who took them to the <term
                    type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119">police</term> detention station in <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName>. Only the <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_ema">wife of
                    Rabbi Perls</persName> was permitted to stay in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-870"
                    type="subject">Jewish hospital</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName>,
                the rest were taken across the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> frontier.</p>

            <p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovak</placeName> authorities declare that they cannot
                allow any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">Jewish refugees</term> from <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> to stay in the country, because, if they do,
                the Nazis would deport all the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>
                <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovakia</placeName>.</p>

            <p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> authorities deported the 51 <term
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> on Tuesday. 35 of them crossed the border into
                    <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> and were arrested by <orgName
                    ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">Nazi stormtroopers</orgName> of <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName> who imprisoned them in one of their barracks. The remaining
                15 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">refugees</term> were yesterday still in the
                Pheasants’ Wood along the border of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName>.</p>

            <p>A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> delegation left <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName> for <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> to ask the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovak</placeName>
                <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110">Minister</term> of the Interior, Dr. <persName
                    ref="#ehri_bf_cerny_josef">Czerny</persName>, to allow the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101"
                    type="subject">Jewish refugees</term> to stay in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html"
                    >Czecho-Slovakia</placeName>. Another delegation is to leave for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2643743/london.html"
                    >London</placeName> to lodge a formal protest with the <placeName
                    ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">British</placeName>
                <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948">Government</term> against such mass expulsions.</p>
